text: The hazel grouse (Tetrastes bonasia), is a type of grouse. It is sometimes called the hazel hen. It is found across the Palearctic as far east as Hokkaid≈ç, and as far west as eastern and central Europe. It lives in dense, damp, mixed coniferous woodland. It is a least concern species. ==References== Category:Phasianidae Category:Birds of Europe Category:Birds of Asia
